verbose_text: According to PCR analysis, the relative mRNA levels of CREPT, cyclin D1, and TCF4 in cervical cancer tissues (0.2846 +/- 0.0780, 0.4013 +/-0.0533, and 0.3822 +/- 0.0533, respectively) were all significantly higher than levels in normal cervical tissues (0.0446 +/- 0.0520, 0.1027 +/- 0.0836, and 0.1322 +/- 0.0641, respectively) (all P < 0.01).
evidence: levels of CREPT, cyclin D1, and TCF4
